'''Morgan Lee Lander''' (born [[January 6]], [[1982]]) is the lead singer and guitarist for the [[Canada|Canadian]] [[alternative metal]] group [[Kittie]]. Her sister, [[Mercedes Lander]], also plays for Kittie. She is known for her use of metal growls as a vocalist, though she often sings with a clean voice.
==Biography==
===Early life=== 
Morgan Lee Lander was born to Dave and Deanna Lander in [[Edmonton, Alberta, Canada]] on [[January 6]], [[1982]]. Two years later, Morgan became the big sister of [[Mercedes Lander]], the drummer and founding members of [[Kittie]].

At the age of two, she moved to [[London, Ontario]]. When Morgan was six, she started to take piano lessons, but soon grew tired and began playing guitar. She started composing her first songs at 13 (including Kittie's breakthrough hit, [[Brackish (song)|Brackish]]) with Mercedes and friend, [[Fallon Bowman]].

===Kittie debut (1996)===
In [[1996]], when Morgan was 14, Mercedes, Fallon, and [[Tanya Candler]] formed [[Kittie]]. Three years later, the band released their breakthrough first album, [[Spit (album)|Spit]].

===Poisoned Black Clothing (2005)===
Morgan is also a successful business woman, she currently co-owns a clothing line called Poisoned Black Clothing with her younger sister, Mercedes. Poisoned Black Clothing officially launched in September 2005, and aims to provide an alternative style for 'cute boys and hot girls'. Morgan also co-owns a management company with her family called X Of Infamy (previously Kiss of Infamy). She currently manages two up-and-coming bands.

==Personal life==
Morgan is currently engaged to Justin Wolfe of [[Canada|Canadian]] band [[Thine Eyes Bleed]].


